wenty-first century and demonstrates the vital role that Xinjiang Han play in national politics—not simply as Beijing’s pawns, but as individuals pursuing their own survival and dreams on the frontier.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aChinesezChinazXinjiang Uygur ZizhiquxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  ahan, china, chinese, people, ethnic group, east asia, cultural ancestry, anthropology, xinjiang, settlers, uyghur, culture, economic repression, motivations, ethnography, oral history, nation building, 21st century, national politics, political concerns, social conditions, institutions, state, mobility, oil elite, stability, traditions, human societies, humanity, development.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022635993940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226360270423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226360270/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles